            Bio
            I’m a postdoc fellow in Health Services Research and
            Development at the Center for Innovations in Quality,
            Effectiveness and Safety, which is associated with the
            Houston VA and Baylor College of Medicine. I received my BA
            in psychology from the University of Maryland, my Masters of
            Science in experimental psychology from Syracuse University,
            and my PhD in cognitive psychology from University of New
            South Wales. My research interests include improving
            diagnostic decision-making, reducing errors in medicine, and
            studying the effects of interruptions and time-pressure on
            medical decision-making.
